</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="351" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[1417,2623,2527,3303]" pageId="5" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1419,2098,3196,3225]" pageId="5" pageNumber="351">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
There is nospecific information available for this species, but Stejneger’s Beaked Whales are known to occur in small groups offive or fewer individuals. The typical composition of these groups remains unclear.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
